Well I'll be darned, the brackets work fine.  I certainly wish it would have told me it didn't like parenthesis!  And thanks for the info, fellows.<br /><br />The last thing in 6502 assembly I did was with that DCC6502 compiler I think, but I believe there was something about it I thought was strange or lacking or I couldn't get used to right away, so I found out about NESASM and have been messing with it ever since, especially since it gave me a familiar feel of working in NASM (8086).  Hopefully I haven't ingrained any of NESASM's tendencies into my brainmeats to the point that one of these others you mentioned would be hard to get used to.<br /><br />Out of curiosity, is NESASM still being developed?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=884">FyberOptic</a> — Wed Aug 16, 2006 9:10 pm</p><hr />
